        "id": "78c5cf53"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Named Entity Recognition (NER) Insights\n",
        "\n",
        "In this analysis, we used NLTK's **Named Entity Chunker** to classify tokens into semantic categories:\n",
        "- **PERSON**: Public figures, CEOs, or athletes.\n",
        "- **ORGANIZATION**: Companies, political parties (e.g., 'Labour', 'BBC'), and sports teams.\n",
        "- **GPE (Geopolitical Entity)**: Countries and cities (e.g., 'UK', 'London').\n",
        "\n",
        "**Key Findings:**\n",
        "- **Relationship Mapping**: By grouping by `Category`, we can see how certain entities are siloed. For instance, 'Labour' appears heavily in **Politics**, while 'Sony' or 'Microsoft' appear in **Tech**.\n",
        "- **Pattern Analysis**: Geopolitical entities (GPE) are highly prevalent across all categories, reflecting the global nature of news reporting."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
