    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "e6f0134b"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Create Prediction Function and Deployment Strategy\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "1. Create a Python function `predict_news_category(text)` that takes raw text as input, preprocesses it using the saved `TfidfVectorizer`, and returns the predicted category using the saved `RandomForestClassifier`.\n",
        "2. Outline a deployment strategy for the NewsBot Intelligence System, considering options like a REST API (e.g., FastAPI, Flask) or integrating into a larger data pipeline.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "eb9264fc"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Final Task\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Summarize the improvements in feature extraction and how n-gram optimization provides better context for the classification models.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "77971d35"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "I will generate a Python code block to create a basic FastAPI application, including necessary imports, NLTK downloads, text preprocessing, model/vectorizer loading, and three endpoints as specified in the instructions: a root endpoint, a prediction endpoint, and a metrics endpoint.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "aec57bc6",
        "outputId": "5e22ece0-5765-41f6-dec2-9f0962a7a55e"
      },
      "source": [
        "import uvicorn\n",
        "from fastapi import FastAPI\n",
        "from pydantic import BaseModel\n",
        "import joblib\n",
        "import re\n",
        "import nltk\n",
        "from nltk.corpus import stopwords\n",
        "from nltk.stem import WordNetLemmatizer\n",
        "from nltk.tokenize import word_tokenize\n",
        "import threading\n",
        "import nest_asyncio\n",
        "\n",
        "# Global variable to track if server is already running\n",
        "# This is a simple mechanism for notebook environments to avoid \"address already in use\" on re-run\n",
        "if 'uvicorn_thread_running' not in globals():\n",
        "    uvicorn_thread_running = False\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Download necessary NLTK data if not already downloaded\n",
        "nltk.download('punkt', quiet=True)\n",
        "nltk.download('stopwords', quiet=True)\n",
        "nltk.download('wordnet', quiet=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))\n",
        "lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Define the preprocess_text function identical to the one used during training\n",
        "def preprocess_text(text):\n",
        "    text = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z\\s]', '', text.lower())\n",
        "    tokens = word_tokenize(text)\n",
        "    cleaned_tokens = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(w) for w in tokens if w not in stop_words]\n",
        "    return ' '.join(cleaned_tokens)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Define the file paths for the saved model and vectorizer\n",
        "MODEL_PATH = 'newsbot_classifier.pkl'\n",
        "VECTORIZER_PATH = 'newsbot_vectorizer.pkl'\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Load the trained RandomForestClassifier model and TfidfVectorizer\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    loaded_model = joblib.load(MODEL_PATH)\n",
        "    loaded_vectorizer = joblib.load(VECTORIZER_PATH)\n",
        "    print(f\"✅ Successfully loaded model from {MODEL_PATH}\")\n",
        "    print(f\"✅ Successfully loaded vectorizer from {VECTORIZER_PATH}\")\n",
        "    model_status = \"Loaded\"\n",
        "except FileNotFoundError:\n",
        "    print(f\"Error: Model or vectorizer file not found. Please ensure {MODEL_PATH} and {VECTORIZER_PATH} exist.\")\n",
        "    loaded_model = None\n",
        "    loaded_vectorizer = None\n",
        "    model_status = \"Error: Files not found\"\n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "    print(f\"Error loading model or vectorizer: {e}\")\n",
        "    loaded_model = None\n",
        "    loaded_vectorizer = None\n",
        "    model_status = f\"Error: {e}\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# 5. Create a FastAPI application instance\n",
        "app = FastAPI()\n",
        "\n",
        "# 6. Define a Pydantic BaseModel for request body validation\n",
        "class TextRequest(BaseModel):\n",
        "    text: str\n",
        "\n",
        "# 7. Implement a POST endpoint /predict\n",
        "@app.post(\"/predict\")\n",
        "async def predict_category(request: TextRequest):\n",
        "    if loaded_model is None or loaded_vectorizer is None:\n",
        "        return {\"error\": \"Models not loaded. Please ensure startup event ran successfully.\"}\n",
        "\n",
        "    cleaned_text = preprocess_text(request.text)\n",
        "    text_tfidf = loaded_vectorizer.transform([cleaned_text])\n",
        "    prediction = loaded_model.predict(text_tfidf)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return {\"predicted_category\": prediction[0]}\n",
        "\n",
        "# 8. Implement a GET endpoint /\n",
        "@app.get(\"/\")\n",
        "async def root():\n",
        "    return {\"message\": \"Welcome to the NewsBot Intelligence System API! Use /predict to get category predictions.\"}\n",
        "\n",
        "# 9. Implement a GET endpoint /metrics\n",
        "@app.get(\"/metrics\")\n",
        "async def metrics():\n",
        "    model_info = {\n",
        "        \"model_name\": \"RandomForestClassifier\",\n",
        "        \"model_status\": model_status,\n",
        "        \"vectorizer_type\": \"TfidfVectorizer\",\n",
        "        \"vectorizer_status\": model_status,\n",
        "        \"num_features\": loaded_vectorizer.max_features if loaded_vectorizer else \"N/A\",\n",
        "        \"ngram_range\": str(loaded_vectorizer.ngram_range) if loaded_vectorizer else \"N/A\"\n",
        "    }\n",
        "    return model_info\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# 10. Start the FastAPI app in a background thread\n",
        "def run_uvicorn():\n",
        "    nest_asyncio.apply()\n",
        "    uvicorn.run(app, host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8000, log_level=\"warning\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Check if the server thread is already running before starting a new one\n",
        "if not uvicorn_thread_running:\n",
        "    print(\"Starting FastAPI app in background...\")\n",
        "    uvicorn_thread = threading.Thread(target=run_uvicorn)\n",
        "    uvicorn_thread.daemon = True # Allow the main program to exit even if the thread is still running\n",
        "    uvicorn_thread.start()\n",
        "    uvicorn_thread_running = True # Set flag to true\n",
        "    print(\"FastAPI app started. It may take a moment for the server to be fully responsive.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"FastAPI app is already running.\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": 87,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "✅ Successfully loaded model from newsbot_classifier.pkl\n",
            "✅ Successfully loaded vectorizer from newsbot_vectorizer.pkl\n",
            "Starting FastAPI app in background...\n",
            "FastAPI app started. It may take a moment for the server to be fully responsive.\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
