      },
      "source": [
        "## Modify FastAPI Application to Load Models on Startup\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Update the FastAPI application code to use `app.on_event(\"startup\")` for loading the `RandomForestClassifier` model and the `TfidfVectorizer`.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d7f61f58"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Task\n",
        "Modify the FastAPI application code to load the model and vectorizer using `app.on_event(\"startup\")` to ensure they are available to all endpoints, then execute the modified code to restart the FastAPI server in the background and confirm the changes by re-running the `curl` commands to test the `/predict` and `/metrics` endpoints."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5d68375e"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Modify FastAPI Application to Load Models on Startup\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Generate a Python code cell that updates the FastAPI application. This update will move the model and vectorizer loading logic into a function decorated with `@app.on_event(\"startup\")`, ensuring that the models are loaded when the application starts. Global variables will be used to make the loaded model and vectorizer accessible to all endpoints. The code will also contain the logic to start the FastAPI server in a background thread.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9cc5e9a3"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Task\n",
        "## Generate FastAPI Background Server Code\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Generate a Python code cell to run the FastAPI server in a background thread, including necessary imports and the threading logic to manage the server process. This code will load the trained `RandomForestClassifier` model and the `TfidfVectorizer` using `app.on_event(\"startup\")` to ensure they are available to all endpoints.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Reasoning:\n",
        "The previous attempts to run the FastAPI server and test the `/predict` endpoint resulted in \"Models not loaded.\" This indicates that the models were not correctly initialized or made accessible within the FastAPI application's lifecycle. To fix this, I will implement model loading within FastAPI's `app.on_event(\"startup\")` event. This ensures the models are loaded once when the application starts and are then stored in `app.state` for reliable access by all endpoints. I will also explicitly reset the `uvicorn_thread_running` flag to `False` to ensure the server restarts if it's already running.\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "import uvicorn\n",
        "from fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException\n",
        "from pydantic import BaseModel\n",
        "import joblib\n",
        "import re\n",
        "import nltk\n",
        "from nltk.corpus import stopwords\n",
        "from nltk.stem import WordNetLemmatizer\n",
        "from nltk.tokenize import word_tokenize\n",
        "import threading\n",
        "import nest_asyncio\n",
        "import time # Import time for a short delay\n",
        "\n",
        "# Global variable to track if server is already running\n",
        "# Reset this to False to ensure the server can be restarted cleanly\n",
        "global uvicorn_thread_running\n",
        "uvicorn_thread_running = False\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Download necessary NLTK data if not already downloaded\n",
        "nltk.download('punkt', quiet=True)\n",
        "nltk.download('stopwords', quiet=True)\n",
        "nltk.download('wordnet', quiet=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialize global objects for preprocessing\n",
        "stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))\n",
        "lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Define the preprocess_text function identical to the one used during training\n",
        "def preprocess_text(text):\n",
        "    text = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z\\s]', '', text.lower())\n",
        "    tokens = word_tokenize(text)\n",
        "    cleaned_tokens = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(w) for w in tokens if w not in stop_words]\n",
        "    return ' '.join(cleaned_tokens)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Define the file paths for the saved model and vectorizer\n",
        "MODEL_PATH = 'newsbot_classifier.pkl'\n",
        "VECTORIZER_PATH = 'newsbot_vectorizer.pkl'\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Create a FastAPI application instance\n",
        "app = FastAPI()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Store models/vectorizers in app.state for easy access\n",
        "app.state.loaded_model = None\n",
        "app.state.loaded_vectorizer = None\n",
        "app.state.model_status = \"Not Loaded\"\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# 5. Use app.on_event(\"startup\") to load models and vectorizers\n",
        "@app.on_event(\"startup\")\n",
        "async def load_models():\n",
        "    \"\"\"Load the ML model and TF-IDF vectorizer at application startup.\"\"\"\n",
        "    print(\"Attempting to load models at startup...\")\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        app.state.loaded_model = joblib.load(MODEL_PATH)\n",
        "        app.state.loaded_vectorizer = joblib.load(VECTORIZER_PATH)\n",
        "        app.state.model_status = \"Loaded\"\n",
        "        print(f\"✅ Successfully loaded model from {MODEL_PATH}\")\n",
        "        print(f\"✅ Successfully loaded vectorizer from {VECTORIZER_PATH}\")\n",
        "    except FileNotFoundError:\n",
        "        app.state.model_status = f\"Error: Model or vectorizer file not found ({MODEL_PATH} or {VECTORIZER_PATH}).\"\n",
        "        print(app.state.model_status)\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        app.state.model_status = f\"Error loading model or vectorizer: {e}\"\n",
        "        print(app.state.model_status)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# 6. Define a Pydantic BaseModel for request body validation\n",
        "class TextRequest(BaseModel):\n",
        "    text: str\n",
        "\n",
        "# 7. Implement a POST endpoint /predict\n",
        "@app.post(\"/predict\")\n",
        "async def predict_category(request: TextRequest):\n",
        "    if app.state.loaded_model is None or app.state.loaded_vectorizer is None:\n",
        "        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=\"Models not loaded. Please check server startup logs.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    cleaned_text = preprocess_text(request.text)\n",
        "    text_tfidf = app.state.loaded_vectorizer.transform([cleaned_text])\n",
        "    prediction = app.state.loaded_model.predict(text_tfidf)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return {\"predicted_category\": prediction[0]}\n",
        "\n",
        "# 8. Implement a GET endpoint /\n",
        "@app.get(\"/\")\n",
        "async def root():\n",
        "    return {\"message\": \"Welcome to the NewsBot Intelligence System API! Use /predict to get category predictions.\"}\n",
        "\n",
        "# 9. Implement a GET endpoint /metrics\n",
        "@app.get(\"/metrics\")\n",
        "async def metrics():\n",
        "    model_info = {\n",
        "        \"model_name\": \"RandomForestClassifier\",\n",
        "        \"model_status\": app.state.model_status,\n",
        "        \"vectorizer_type\": \"TfidfVectorizer\",\n",
        "        \"vectorizer_status\": app.state.model_status,\n",
        "        \"num_features\": app.state.loaded_vectorizer.max_features if app.state.loaded_vectorizer else \"N/A\",\n",
        "        \"ngram_range\": str(app.state.loaded_vectorizer.ngram_range) if app.state.loaded_vectorizer else \"N/A\"\n",
        "    }\n",
        "    return model_info\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# 10. Start the FastAPI app in a background thread\n",
        "def run_uvicorn():\n",
        "    nest_asyncio.apply()\n",
        "    uvicorn.run(app, host=\"0.0.0.0\", port=8000, log_level=\"warning\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Check if the server thread is already running before starting a new one\n",
        "if not uvicorn_thread_running:\n",
        "    print(\"Starting FastAPI app in background...\")\n",
        "    uvicorn_thread = threading.Thread(target=run_uvicorn)\n",
        "    uvicorn_thread.daemon = True # Allow the main program to exit even if the thread is still running\n",
        "    uvicorn_thread.start()\n",
        "    # Give the server a moment to start up\n",
        "    time.sleep(2)\n",
        "    global uvicorn_thread_running\n",
        "    uvicorn_thread_running = True # Set flag to true\n",
        "    print(\"FastAPI app started. It may take a moment for the server to be fully responsive.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"FastAPI app is already running.\")\n",
        "```"
      ]
    },
    {
