      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "43abbd2e"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Fix Curl Command Syntax\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Modify the `curl` commands in the existing code cell (`bf179cfe`) to correctly escape the double quotes within the JSON payload for the `-d` argument. This will ensure the JSON is parsed correctly by the shell.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4b12dbbb"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Task\n",
        "## Execute Fixed Curl Commands\n",
        "\n",
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "The previous `curl` commands resulted in a `curl: (3) URL using bad/illegal format or missing URL` error for POST requests, despite the FastAPI server apparently receiving the requests. This often indicates shell parsing issues with complex quoted strings. To address the instruction of \"correctly escaping the double quotes within the JSON payload\", and to robustly handle the `curl` command within the `!` context, I will replace the single-quoted JSON payloads with double-quoted payloads where inner double quotes are escaped (`-d \"{\\\"key\\\": \\\"value\\\"}\"`). This is a more standard and often more robust way to pass JSON in shell commands. This change will also implicitly simplify the shell command by making it a single logical line, which may further prevent parsing errors.\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "print(f\"Testing /predict endpoint with a sports article on port {FASTAPI_PORT}...\")\n",
        "!curl -X POST \"http://0.0.0.0:{FASTAPI_PORT}/predict\" \\\n",
        "     -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n",
        "     -d \"{\\\"text\\\": \\\"LeBron James led the Lakers to victory with a triple-double performance last night.\\\"}\"\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nTesting /predict endpoint with a business article on port {FASTAPI_PORT}...\")\n",
        "!curl -X POST \"http://0.0.0.0:{FASTAPI_PORT}/predict\" \\\n",
        "     -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n",
        "     -d \"{\\\"text\\\": \\\"The stock market saw a surge today after positive economic data was released.\\\"}\"\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nTesting /metrics endpoint on port {FASTAPI_PORT}...\")\n",
        "!curl \"http://0.0.0.0:{FASTAPI_PORT}/metrics\"\n",
        "```"
      ]
    },
