    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2e4bc5c5"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Summary:\n",
        "\n",
        "### Data Analysis Key Findings\n",
        "*   The FastAPI server's `/predict` and `/metrics` endpoints were successfully tested.\n",
        "*   The model correctly classified sample \"sport\" and \"business\" articles.\n",
        "*   A \"tech\" article about \"AI breakthrough\" was **incorrectly classified as \"sport\"**.\n",
        "*   The `/metrics` endpoint confirmed the model as a `RandomForestClassifier` and the vectorizer as `TfidfVectorizer` with 5000 features and an `ngram_range` of (1, 3).\n",
        "*   The top 10 TF-IDF features for the 'TECH' category included: `mobile, phone, people, said, technology, game, user, service, software, computer`.\n",
        "*   The top 10 TF-IDF features for the 'SPORT' category included: `game, england, win, player, said, match, champion, cup, team, chelsea`.\n",
        "*   Crucially, while 'game' appeared in the top features for both 'TECH' and 'SPORT', the misclassified \"tech\" article (\"New AI breakthrough promises faster processing of large datasets and revolutionizes machine learning\") **did not contain the word 'game'**.\n",
        "*   The misclassified \"tech\" article's highly indicative terms like 'ai', 'breakthrough', 'processing', 'datasets', and 'machine learning' were *not* among the top 10 TF-IDF features for the 'TECH' category, which skewed towards more general consumer tech terms.\n",
        "*   The misclassified article entirely lacked any strong sport-specific indicators found in the top 'SPORT' features (e.g., 'england', 'win', 'player').\n",
        "\n",
        "### Insights or Next Steps\n",
        "*   The current TF-IDF feature set, despite using n-grams, appears to be insufficient in capturing the nuanced vocabulary of advanced \"tech\" subcategories like AI and machine learning. This limitation leads to misclassifications when articles use less common but highly specific terminology not well-represented in the dominant features.\n",
        "*   To improve classification accuracy for specialized \"tech\" content, consider re-evaluating the `TfidfVectorizer`'s parameters (e.g., `ngram_range`, `max_features`) or incorporating domain-specific keywords and embeddings to better represent niche topics. Further analysis into the model's feature importances and the specific weights of words within misclassified articles would also be beneficial.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "b0d6553f"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Task\n",
        "Okay, I will execute the Python script from cell `96ebcd1e` to test the FastAPI endpoints.\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "import requests\n",
        "import json\n",
        "\n",
        "# Ensure FASTAPI_PORT is defined globally from the server startup cell\n",
        "if 'FASTAPI_PORT' not in globals():\n",
        "    print(\"Error: FASTAPI_PORT not found. Please ensure the FastAPI server cell was run.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    base_url = f\"http://0.0.0.0:{FASTAPI_PORT}\"\n",
        "    predict_url = f\"{base_url}/predict\"\n",
        "    metrics_url = f\"{base_url}/metrics\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    print(f\"Base URL for API testing: {base_url}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Sample texts for prediction\n",
        "    sample_articles = {\n",
        "        \"sport\": \"LeBron James led the Lakers to victory with a triple-double performance last night.\",\n",
        "        \"business\": \"The stock market saw a surge today after positive economic data was released.\",\n",
        "        \"tech\": \"New AI breakthrough promises faster processing of large datasets and revolutionizes machine learning.\"\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Test /predict endpoint\n",
        "    print(\"\\n--- Testing /predict endpoint ---\")\n",
        "    for category_hint, text in sample_articles.items():\n",
        "        print(f\"Testing with a {category_hint} article...\")\n",
        "        payload = {\"text\": text}\n",
        "        headers = {'Content-Type': 'application/json'}\n",
        "        try:\n",
        "            response = requests.post(predict_url, data=json.dumps(payload), headers=headers)\n",
        "            response.raise_for_status() # Raise an exception for HTTP errors\n",
        "            print(f\"Response for {category_hint} article: {response.json()}\")\n",
        "        except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e:\n",
        "            print(f\"Error making request for {category_hint} article: {e}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Test /metrics endpoint\n",
        "    print(\"\\n--- Testing /metrics endpoint ---\")\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        response = requests.get(metrics_url)\n",
        "        response.raise_for_status()\n",
        "        print(f\"Response from /metrics: {response.json()}\")\n",
        "    except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e:\n",
        "        print(f\"Error making request to /metrics: {e}\")\n",
        "```\n",
        "```\n",
        "Base URL for API testing: http://0.0.0.0:40315\n",
        "\n",
        "--- Testing /predict endpoint ---\n",
        "Testing with a sport article...\n",
        "Response for sport article: {'predicted_category': 'sport'}\n",
        "Testing with a business article...\n",
        "Response for business article: {'predicted_category': 'business'}\n",
        "Testing with a tech article...\n",
        "Response for tech article: {'predicted_category': 'sport'}\n",
        "\n",
        "--- Testing /metrics endpoint ---\n",
        "Response from /metrics: {'model_name': 'RandomForestClassifier', 'model_status': 'Loaded', 'vectorizer_type': 'TfidfVectorizer', 'vectorizer_status': 'Loaded', 'num_features': 5000, 'ngram_range': '(1, 3)'}\n",
        "```\n",
