        "id": "cba7f6a4"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Analyze Confusion Matrix for Tech and Sport\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Extract the relevant sub-matrix for 'tech' and 'sport' from the `cm_ngrams_1_3` confusion matrix. Based on the alphabetical order of categories ('business', 'entertainment', 'politics', 'sport', 'tech') in the classification report, 'sport' is at index 3 and 'tech' is at index 4. Interpret the values within this sub-matrix, specifically identifying True Positives, False Positives, and False Negatives for both categories, and any inter-category misclassifications.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ed8c4f7f"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "To analyze the confusion matrix for 'sport' and 'tech', I will first explicitly define the category order, then extract the relevant sub-matrix from `cm_ngrams_1_3` and calculate True Positives, False Positives, and False Negatives for both categories, along with their inter-category misclassifications.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "93907cfe",
        "outputId": "ba450e17-e471-4109-cbed-1348f4a43a23"
      },
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Define the category order to correctly interpret the confusion matrix\n",
        "# This order is derived from the classification report classes (usually alphabetical)\n",
        "category_order = ['business', 'entertainment', 'politics', 'sport', 'tech']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Find indices for 'sport' and 'tech'\n",
        "sport_idx = category_order.index('sport') # Should be 3\n",
        "tech_idx = category_order.index('tech')   # Should be 4\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Category order: {category_order}\")\n",
        "print(f\"'Sport' index: {sport_idx}\")\n",
        "print(f\"'Tech' index: {tech_idx}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Print the full confusion matrix for context\n",
        "print(f\"\\nFull Confusion Matrix (cm_ngrams_1_3):\\n{cm_ngrams_1_3}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Extract the 2x2 sub-matrix for 'sport' and 'tech'\n",
        "# Rows are actual, columns are predicted\n",
        "# The sub-matrix will be for [sport, tech] rows and [sport, tech] columns\n",
        "sub_matrix_indices = [sport_idx, tech_idx]\n",
        "sub_matrix = cm_ngrams_1_3[sub_matrix_indices][:, sub_matrix_indices]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nSub-matrix for 'Sport' and 'Tech' (Actual rows, Predicted columns):\\n{sub_matrix}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Interpret values for 'sport' (index 3)\n",
        "# True Positives: Actual Sport, Predicted Sport\n",
        "tp_sport = cm_ngrams_1_3[sport_idx, sport_idx]\n",
        "\n",
        "# False Positives for Sport: Predicted Sport, but actually another category\n",
        "fp_sport = cm_ngrams_1_3[:, sport_idx].sum() - tp_sport\n",
        "\n",
        "# False Negatives for Sport: Actual Sport, but predicted as another category\n",
        "fn_sport = cm_ngrams_1_3[sport_idx, :].sum() - tp_sport\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\n--- Analysis for 'Sport' ---\")\n",
        "print(f\"True Positives (Actual Sport, Predicted Sport): {tp_sport}\")\n",
        "print(f\"False Positives (Predicted Sport, Actual other categories): {fp_sport}\")\n",
        "print(f\"False Negatives (Actual Sport, Predicted other categories): {fn_sport}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Interpret values for 'tech' (index 4)\n",
        "# True Positives: Actual Tech, Predicted Tech\n",
        "tp_tech = cm_ngrams_1_3[tech_idx, tech_idx]\n",
        "\n",
        "# False Positives for Tech: Predicted Tech, but actually another category\n",
        "fp_tech = cm_ngrams_1_3[:, tech_idx].sum() - tp_tech\n",
        "\n",
        "# False Negatives for Tech: Actual Tech, but predicted as another category\n",
        "fn_tech = cm_ngrams_1_3[tech_idx, :].sum() - tp_tech\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\n--- Analysis for 'Tech' ---\")\n",
        "print(f\"True Positives (Actual Tech, Predicted Tech): {tp_tech}\")\n",
        "print(f\"False Positives (Predicted Tech, Actual other categories): {fp_tech}\")\n",
        "print(f\"False Negatives (Actual Tech, Predicted other categories): {fn_tech}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 5. Specifically identify inter-category misclassifications\n",
        "# Actual 'sport' but predicted as 'tech'\n",
        "sport_to_tech = cm_ngrams_1_3[sport_idx, tech_idx]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Actual 'tech' but predicted as 'sport'\n",
        "tech_to_sport = cm_ngrams_1_3[tech_idx, sport_idx]\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\n--- Inter-Category Misclassifications ---\")\n",
        "print(f\"Articles that were Actual 'sport' but predicted as 'tech': {sport_to_tech}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Articles that were Actual 'tech' but predicted as 'sport': {tech_to_sport}\")\n"
      ],
      "execution_count": 102,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Category order: ['business', 'entertainment', 'politics', 'sport', 'tech']\n",
            "'Sport' index: 3\n",
            "'Tech' index: 4\n",
            "\n",
            "Full Confusion Matrix (cm_ngrams_1_3):\n",
            "[[64  0  2  1  0]\n",
            " [ 1 52  0  1  1]\n",
            " [ 3  0 50  1  1]\n",
            " [ 1  0  0 68  0]\n",
            " [ 3  1  0  0 48]]\n",
            "\n",
            "Sub-matrix for 'Sport' and 'Tech' (Actual rows, Predicted columns):\n",
            "[[68  0]\n",
            " [ 0 48]]\n",
            "\n",
            "--- Analysis for 'Sport' ---\n",
            "True Positives (Actual Sport, Predicted Sport): 68\n",
            "False Positives (Predicted Sport, Actual other categories): 3\n",
            "False Negatives (Actual Sport, Predicted other categories): 1\n",
            "\n",
            "--- Analysis for 'Tech' ---\n",
            "True Positives (Actual Tech, Predicted Tech): 48\n",
            "False Positives (Predicted Tech, Actual other categories): 2\n",
            "False Negatives (Actual Tech, Predicted other categories): 4\n",
            "\n",
            "--- Inter-Category Misclassifications ---\n",
