      "source": [
        "## Define and Implement get_most_frequent_terms Function\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Create a Python function `get_most_frequent_terms` to extract and display the most frequent terms (including n-grams) per category based on TF-IDF scores.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d757c255"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "I will define the `get_most_frequent_terms` function as specified, iterating through categories, calculating mean TF-IDF scores for features, and then printing the top N terms for each category.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "d9cc81c7",
        "outputId": "3c03bb00-3bf0-44de-a751-d2b74a27b161"
      },
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "def get_most_frequent_terms(df, tfidf_matrix, feature_names, top_n=10):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Extracts and displays the most frequent terms (including n-grams) per category\n",
        "    based on TF-IDF scores.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Args:\n",
        "        df (pd.DataFrame): DataFrame containing 'Category' and 'cleaned_text' columns.\n",
        "        tfidf_matrix (scipy.sparse.csr_matrix): The TF-IDF matrix.\n",
        "        feature_names (list): List of feature names corresponding to the TF-IDF matrix columns.\n",
        "        top_n (int, optional): The number of top terms to display per category. Defaults to 10.\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    print(f\"\\nTop {top_n} Most Frequent Terms per Category (including N-grams):\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    for category in df['Category'].unique():\n",
        "        # a. Obtain the indices of rows in df that belong to the current category.\n",
        "        category_indices = df[df['Category'] == category].index\n",
        "\n",
        "        # b. Use these indices to create a category_matrix by slicing the tfidf_matrix.\n",
        "        category_matrix = tfidf_matrix[category_indices]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # c. Calculate the mean TF-IDF score for each feature across the category_matrix.\n",
        "        mean_weights = np.asarray(category_matrix.mean(axis=0)).ravel()\n",
        "\n",
        "        # d. Find the indices of the top top_n features with the highest mean TF-IDF scores.\n",
        "        top_indices = mean_weights.argsort()[::-1][:top_n]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # e. Retrieve the actual feature names (terms) using these indices from feature_names.\n",
        "        top_terms = [feature_names[i] for i in top_indices]\n",
        "\n",
        "        # f. Print the category name followed by its top top_n terms.\n",
        "        print(f\"[{category.upper()}]: {', '.join(top_terms)}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Call the function with the n-gram TF-IDF data\n",
        "get_most_frequent_terms(df, tfidf_matrix_ngrams, feature_names_ngrams)"
      ],
      "execution_count": 104,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "\n",
            "Top 10 Most Frequent Terms per Category (including N-grams):\n",
            "\n",
            "[BUSINESS]: bn, said, firm, company, market, bank, growth, year, economy, sale\n",
            "[TECH]: mobile, phone, people, said, technology, game, user, service, software, computer\n",
            "[POLITICS]: mr, said, labour, election, blair, party, government, tory, would, minister\n",
            "[SPORT]: game, england, win, player, said, match, champion, cup, team, chelsea\n",
            "[ENTERTAINMENT]: film, award, best, show, star, music, band, said, actor, year\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
