        "## Develop Production Monitoring Plan\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Outline key metrics and strategies for continuously monitoring the NewsBot Intelligence System in a production environment.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9a476c6b"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Production Monitoring Plan for NewsBot Intelligence System\n",
        "\n",
        "To ensure the NewsBot Intelligence System operates reliably, efficiently, and maintains its predictive accuracy in a production environment, a comprehensive monitoring plan is essential. This plan focuses on tracking performance, identifying issues proactively, and informing continuous improvement.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 1. Key Metrics to Monitor\n",
        "\n",
        "#### A. Model Performance Metrics:\n",
        "*   **Prediction Accuracy/F1-score:** Track overall and per-category accuracy/F1-score on a continuously evaluated validation set (e.g., daily stream of manually labeled data or expert-reviewed samples).\n",
        "*   **Data Drift:** Monitor changes in input data distribution (e.g., TF-IDF feature distributions, word frequencies, article length) compared to training data. Significant shifts can indicate the need for retraining.\n",
        "*   **Concept Drift:** Monitor changes in the relationship between input features and target categories. A decline in accuracy on recent data, even with stable input distribution, suggests concept drift.\n",
        "*   **Prediction Confidence:** Track the distribution of model prediction probabilities. A drop in average confidence could signal emerging issues.\n",
        "\n",
        "#### B. System Health Metrics:\n",
        "*   **API Latency:** Monitor the response time for `/predict` and `/metrics` endpoints. High latency indicates performance bottlenecks.\n",
        "*   **Error Rates:** Track the frequency of HTTP errors (e.g., 4xx, 5xx) and internal application errors.\n",
        "*   **Uptime/Availability:** Ensure the API endpoints are consistently reachable and responsive.\n",
        "*   **Request Volume:** Monitor the number of incoming prediction requests to gauge system load and usage patterns.\n",
        "\n",
        "#### C. Resource Utilization Metrics:\n",
        "*   **CPU Utilization:** Track CPU usage of the FastAPI application and underlying system.\n",
        "*   **Memory Usage:** Monitor memory consumption to detect leaks or inefficient resource allocation.\n",
        "*   **Disk I/O:** Monitor disk reads/writes, especially important for models that frequently load/save data.\n",
        "*   **Network Throughput:** Track network traffic for the API service.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 2. Monitoring Tools/Strategies\n",
        "\n",
        "*   **Metrics Collection (Prometheus):** Use Prometheus to collect time-series metrics directly from the FastAPI application (e.g., using `prometheus_client` library for custom metrics like `PREDICTION_COUNT`, `PREDICTION_LATENCY`) and infrastructure (node exporter).\n",
        "*   **Dashboarding (Grafana):** Visualize collected metrics using Grafana dashboards for real-time operational oversight, trend analysis, and historical data review.\n",
        "*   **Logging (ELK Stack - Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana):** Collect, parse, and store structured application logs (e.g., using `pythonjsonlogger` for JSON formatted logs) in Elasticsearch. Use Kibana for searching, analyzing, and visualizing log data to troubleshoot errors and understand user behavior.\n",
        "*   **Tracing (OpenTelemetry/Jaeger):** Implement distributed tracing to monitor requests across microservices, identifying bottlenecks in complex architectures.\n",
        "*   **Model Observability (MLflow/Weights & Biases):** Track model versions, training runs, and performance metrics over time to facilitate model governance and rollback capabilities.\n",
        "*   **A/B Testing:** For new model versions or feature engineering, deploy in a canary release or A/B test setup to compare performance metrics against the current production model before full rollout.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 3. Alerting Mechanisms\n",
        "\n",
        "*   **Threshold-Based Alerts:** Configure alerts in Prometheus Alertmanager (integrated with Grafana) to trigger when metrics exceed predefined thresholds (e.g., API latency > 500ms, error rate > 5%, accuracy drop > 2%).\n",
        "*   **Anomaly Detection Alerts:** Employ machine learning-based anomaly detection on key metrics to catch subtle deviations that might not cross static thresholds.\n",
        "*   **Escalation Policies:** Define clear escalation paths for alerts:\n",
        "    *   **Critical Errors (PagerDuty/On-call Rotation):** Immediate notification for major service outages, high error rates, or significant model degradation.\n",
        "    *   **Warnings (Slack/Microsoft Teams):** Notifications for moderate performance dips, unusual request patterns, or minor data drift, typically sent to development/MLOps channels.\n",
        "    *   **Informational (Email/Daily Reports):** Summaries of daily performance, resource utilization, and successful events.\n",
        "\n",
        "### 4. Actionable Insights\n",
        "\n",
        "*   **Model Retraining:** Consistent drops in prediction accuracy, significant data drift, or concept drift will automatically trigger an investigation and potentially kick off a model retraining pipeline.\n",
        "*   **Infrastructure Scaling:** High CPU/memory utilization or increasing API latency will signal the need for autoscaling (if deployed on cloud platforms) or manual scaling adjustments.\n",
        "*   **Anomaly Detection:** Unexplained spikes in error rates or unusual prediction distributions will lead to immediate deep dives into logs and traces to identify root causes (e.g., malformed requests, dependency issues, data quality problems).\n",
        "*   **Performance Optimization:** Detailed latency metrics and profiling data can pinpoint inefficient code paths or resource-intensive operations requiring optimization.\n",
        "*   **Feature Engineering/Data Collection:** Analysis of misclassified articles and features contributing to data/concept drift can inform the development of new features or improved data collection strategies."
      ]
    },
