        "## Implement Advanced Feature Engineering\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Refine the feature extraction process by implementing the proposed strategies such as creating domain-specific lexicons, integrating Named Entity Recognition (NER) outputs as features, and incorporating sentiment analysis scores to improve the model's ability to differentiate between confusing categories (e.g., Business, Tech, Entertainment, Politics).\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2eb62872"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "The first step is to define domain-specific lexicons for each category based on common terms, as instructed.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "d079840c",
        "outputId": "7dc2c75d-b8ae-43e5-f329-776dded28ed7"
      },
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Define domain-specific lexicons\n",
        "# These are based on observed top TF-IDF terms and general domain knowledge\n",
        "\n",
        "business_lexicon = [\n",
        "    'bank', 'market', 'company', 'firm', 'economy', 'economic', 'growth', 'deal',\n",
        "    'share', 'invest', 'profit', 'loss', 'billion', 'million', 'quarter', 'sector', 'trade'\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "tech_lexicon = [\n",
        "    'mobile', 'phone', 'technology', 'tech', 'software', 'computer', 'internet', 'web',\n",
        "    'digital', 'network', 'device', 'app', 'data', 'security', 'cyber', 'ai', 'machine learning'\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "politics_lexicon = [\n",
        "    'government', 'party', 'election', 'minister', 'parliament', 'vote', 'political',\n",
        "    'policy', 'prime minister', 'labour', 'tory', 'leader', 'campaign', 'parliamentary'\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "sport_lexicon = [\n",
        "    'game', 'match', 'team', 'player', 'club', 'league', 'championship', 'world cup',\n",
        "    'football', 'rugby', 'cricket', 'olympic', 'medal', 'win', 'defeat', 'coach', 'sporting'\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "entertainment_lexicon = [\n",
        "    'film', 'movie', 'actor', 'actress', 'star', 'music', 'band', 'album', 'show',\n",
        "    'tv', 'television', 'award', 'festival', 'celebrity', 'artist', 'song', 'chart'\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Combine into a dictionary for easy access\n",
        "lexicons = {\n",
        "    'business': business_lexicon,\n",
        "    'tech': tech_lexicon,\n",
        "    'politics': politics_lexicon,\n",
        "    'sport': sport_lexicon,\n",
        "    'entertainment': entertainment_lexicon\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Lexicons defined for all categories.\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": 107,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Lexicons defined for all categories.\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "813c3383"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "Now that lexicons are defined, I will create functions to count the occurrences of terms from each lexicon in the 'cleaned_text' column and add these counts as new features to the DataFrame.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 330
        },
        "id": "0d95f2b8",
        "outputId": "b727cc3f-82a7-4bbd-e67a-025d8bc1bd53"
      },
      "source": [
        "import re\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Create functions to calculate new features based on lexicons\n",
        "def count_lexicon_terms(text, lexicon):\n",
        "    count = 0\n",
        "    for term in lexicon:\n",
        "        # Use word boundaries to avoid partial matches (e.g., 'car' matching 'carpet')\n",
        "        count += len(re.findall(r'\\b' + re.escape(term) + r'\\b', text, re.IGNORECASE))\n",
        "    return count\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Calculating lexicon-based features...\")\n",
        "for category, lexicon in lexicons.items():\n",
        "    col_name = f'{category}_lexicon_count'\n",
        "    df[col_name] = df['cleaned_text'].apply(lambda x: count_lexicon_terms(x, lexicon))\n",
        "    print(f\"Added '{col_name}' column.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Display the first few rows with the new features\n",
        "display(df[['ArticleId', 'Category', 'business_lexicon_count', 'tech_lexicon_count',\n",
        "            'politics_lexicon_count', 'sport_lexicon_count', 'entertainment_lexicon_count']].head())"
      ],
      "execution_count": 108,
