    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d2c6d3e2"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Generate BERT Embeddings for Articles\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Develop a function to take cleaned text as input, tokenize it using the BERT tokenizer, pass it through the BERT model, and extract a fixed-size embedding (e.g., the [CLS] token embedding or averaged token embeddings) for each article. This process will create a new set of high-dimensional features.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "1fab15b8"
      },
      "source": [
        "## Combine BERT Embeddings with Existing Features\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Integrate the newly generated BERT embeddings with the existing `combined_scaled_features` (which includes TF-IDF, lexicon counts, NER counts, and sentiment scores) into a unified feature matrix.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "72702493"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "I will convert the `bert_embeddings` from the DataFrame column into a NumPy array and then combine it with the `combined_scaled_features` using `hstack` to create `final_combined_features`. I will print the shape to verify the concatenation.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "73e0d38a",
        "outputId": "07f8dba2-bf34-4770-f3d7-367992ab29e8"
      },
      "source": [
        "from scipy.sparse import hstack, csr_matrix\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Combining BERT embeddings with existing features...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Convert bert_embeddings from DataFrame column to a NumPy array\n",
        "# Ensure bert_embeddings is a 2D array compatible for stacking\n",
        "bert_embeddings_array = np.vstack(df['bert_embeddings'].values)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Convert bert_embeddings_array to a sparse matrix for consistent stacking if combined_scaled_features is sparse\n",
        "# It's generally better to convert the dense BERT embeddings to sparse if the other matrix is sparse to maintain sparsity\n",
        "# However, hstack handles mixed dense/sparse, so we can stick to dense here and let hstack promote to sparse if needed,\n",
        "# or explicitly convert both to sparse.\n",
        "# Given combined_scaled_features is sparse (csr_matrix), convert BERT embeddings to csr_matrix as well.\n",
        "bert_embeddings_sparse = csr_matrix(bert_embeddings_array)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Combine the combined_scaled_features (sparse) with the bert_embeddings_sparse\n",
        "# combined_scaled_features was generated in cell `73feee38`\n",
        "final_combined_features = hstack([combined_scaled_features, bert_embeddings_sparse])\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Print the shape of the final_combined_features matrix\n",
        "print(f\"Shape of BERT embeddings: {bert_embeddings_array.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Shape of existing combined_scaled_features: {combined_scaled_features.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"✅ Final Combined Feature Matrix Shape: {final_combined_features.shape}\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": 133,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Combining BERT embeddings with existing features...\n",
            "Shape of BERT embeddings: (1490, 768)\n",
            "Shape of existing combined_scaled_features: (1490, 5010)\n",
            "✅ Final Combined Feature Matrix Shape: (1490, 5778)\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "e61e0dad"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "I will generate a Python code block to split the dataset, train a RandomForestClassifier with the combined features including BERT embeddings, and evaluate its performance using a classification report and confusion matrix, as requested by the instructions.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 942
        },
        "id": "86cfebe9",
        "outputId": "48d8823d-6948-4f99-9a57-33d9c5a85439"
      },
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Split the dataset with the new combined features (including BERT embeddings)\n",
        "# X will be final_combined_features, y will be df['Category']\n",
        "X_bert = final_combined_features\n",
        "y_bert = df['Category']\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train_bert, X_test_bert, y_train_bert, y_test_bert = train_test_split(\n",
        "    X_bert, y_bert, test_size=0.2, random_state=42, stratify=y_bert\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Data split into training and testing sets with BERT embeddings.\")\n",
        "print(f\"X_train_bert shape: {X_train_bert.shape}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Instantiate a RandomForestClassifier\n",
        "rf_model_bert = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Train the RandomForestClassifier\n",
        "print(\"\\nTraining RandomForestClassifier with BERT embeddings...\")\n",
        "rf_model_bert.fit(X_train_bert, y_train_bert)\n",
        "print(\"RandomForestClassifier trained successfully.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Make predictions on the test set\n",
        "y_pred_bert = rf_model_bert.predict(X_test_bert)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 5. Print a detailed classification_report\n",
        "print(\"\\nModel Evaluation Report (with BERT Embeddings):\\n\")\n",
        "print(classification_report(y_test_bert, y_pred_bert))\n",
        "\n",
        "# 6. Generate and visualize a confusion_matrix as a heatmap\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 7))\n",
        "cm_bert = confusion_matrix(y_test_bert, y_pred_bert)\n",
        "sns.heatmap(cm_bert, annot=True, fmt='d', xticklabels=rf_model_bert.classes_, yticklabels=rf_model_bert.classes_, cmap='Blues')\n",
        "plt.title('Confusion Matrix (BERT Embeddings): Predicted vs Actual Category')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Actual Category')\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Predicted Category')\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
